OL,3,C'Find the words' - the push to get
OL,4,Cpeople talking about baby loss
OL,6,F"After the initial loss, which is
OL,7,Fabsolutely devastating," Ruth said,
OL,8,F"people are either completely silent,
OL,9,Fwhich makes parents feel even more
OL,10,Fisolated, or they tend to clutch a
OL,11,Fquite negative positivity."
OL,13,FShe found support through Sands and
OL,14,Fbecame a volunteer 'befriender' for
OL,15,FMerthyr Sands, a support group for
OL,16,Fbereaved parents in the area.
