OL,3,C'Find the words' - the push to get
OL,4,Cpeople talking about baby loss
OL,6,FThe charity says the majority of
OL,7,Fparents who do have the opportunity to
OL,8,Ftalk about their loss feel relieved to
OL,9,Fbe able to talk about what happened
OL,10,Fand that a weight has been 'lifted
OL,11,Ffrom their shoulders'.
OL,13,FRuth says parents often feel isolated
OL,14,Fand lonely after losing a child, so
OL,15,Fhaving the right people around them
OL,16,Fwho can say the right thing is very
OL,17,Fimportant.
